Job Description
Our client has been awarded the annual shutdown contract for a major refinery in the UAE, and require a technically sound HSE Manager to lead and oversee the activity of the HSE team running this project.
Qualified to degree level as a minimum, applicants will need to have an excellent track record working on similar projects, whilst also having a safety diploma from a recognised body. Membership of IOSH or CSP will be highly regarded.
As a senior figure on the team, the job holder will have demonstrable experience in a managerial capacity being based on shutdown and turnaround projects, ideally from a downstream background. This experience must also include major, easily recognisable assets within Oil and Gas.
On offer is a competitive, tax free salary, alongside a single status package consisting of housing, transportation and insurance.
Qualifications
Bachelors Degree or equivalent
